element.name: T is for Traffic by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: Get a clear view of the traffic - which has replaced, church politics and taxes as the most popular topic of conversation in Dublin, especially if it's the "Mad Cow" or M50.

ul.li:
2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by BlueFoxPL
Another great day for caching... found with some friends. TFTC.

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by colmyster
Took ages to find this one. TFTC

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by Wicca Cailín
Nicely hidden, took us a while, turned out to be right beside us the whole time. TFTC.

2010-05-25T19:00:00Z : Found it by Sam4444
Took us a while to locate this one but eventually we did! [8D]

2010-05-25T19:00:00Z : Found it by oldnavycarl
Last one of four caches for us this evening. Took in a lovely sun set from here. Took a little while to find but got it - was not going to leave without finding it! Thanks Hezekiah!

2007-09-06T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
CMB50 and I decided to make use of the hire car for another day. We parked at the lookout and admired the view before heading to the cache. After deciding that the traffic was too heavy and fast-moving to be bothered with us we found it very quickly. TNLNSL
